#: ../../source/overview.rst:2
#: 7781ae90e4344eaebb39ced9d6924534
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:4
#: 955b97dc0830467881118aec54ddd7d0
msgid "**FS_GPlib** is a flexible and scalable Python library designed for simulating a wide range of graph-based propagation processes. It supports classical epidemic models, opinion dynamics, and simulations on dynamic networks. The library is built to facilitate high-efficiency simulation through support for Message Passing based dual-acceleration framework and distributed computing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:6
#: f21d58cab78b4e8c95e6c0577c6d1ddb
msgid "This documentation provides a structured overview of FS_GPlib, from installation and usage to the implementation of custom models. Whether you're a researcher studying network diffusion or a developer looking to integrate propagation models into your pipeline, FS_GPlib offers a modular and extensible foundation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:9
#: cbc6536e7a7f4521b5ee9e4a8126bfad
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:11
#: 309d13e9e3f447f8b1d173c02f07c945
msgid "Propagation models are essential tools in understanding how information, behaviors, or diseases spread through complex networks. FS_GPlib is developed to address the following challenges:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:13
#: 0b1b714459344204b97fe2ee0e4f3fff
msgid "The need for **efficient simulation** on large-scale graphs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:14
#: 79a03ef2134a4ac0ae2eec69fcd5f15f
msgid "The demand for **modular design** that supports custom models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:15
#: ef7807aa05914bb0a92089386fb1ae7a
msgid "The importance of **distributed simulation** to overcome scalability bottlenecks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:18
#: 9e5e5457d6644c82a52156d406810eda
msgid "Core Capabilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:20
#: 7835fd8d79a14cc7a941588817339618
msgid "**Model Support**: Built-in support for classical epidemic models (SI, SIS, SIR), opinion dynamics, and network evolution processes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:21
#: 6af7d4e460734a6fba0cbc3d82721bc4
msgid "**Batch Simulation**: Perform multiple simulations in parallel using high-dimensional tensor operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:22
#: abff24da8a7843169ad20643c26cfb19
msgid "**Distributed Execution**: Supports graph partitioning to enable distribution across multiple processors or nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/overview.rst:23
#: a59f196c8d1e4072803449b2b566e3f9
msgid "**Extensibility**: Easily implement your own propagation rules through the custom model interface."
msgstr ""

